other_tests.findings: Severe hypoplasia of the anterior pituitary and corpus callosum, decreased white matter bulk.
Subnormal GH and cortisol responses in four of five children tested.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Peak serum GH responses were highest in the youngest children and much lower in the older children, indicating possible progression of GH secretion failure.

other_tests.findings: Suboptimal cortisol response in one of three patients tested.
